FT  06 MAR 93 / Iran urged to sever UK links
IRAN was urged yesterday to cancel trade agreements with Britain because of
the row over the author Salman Rushdie, writes Roger Matthews in London.
Speaking at Friday prayers in Tehran, Ayatollah Ahmad Jannati, one of Iran's
most outspoken clerics, said parliament should review economic and trade
relations with Britain because of its insults to Islam.
